bilingual.source: Teachers, parents, and students need to value effort, not intelligence.
bilingual.target: 老师、家长和学生需要重视努力，而不是智力。

bilingual.source: His level of intelligence is very high.
Scientists study the intelligence of the octopus.
bilingual.target: 科学家研究章鱼的智力。

bilingual.source: This test can measure your intelligence level.
bilingual.target: 这个测试可以测量你的智力水平。

bilingual.source: She has remarkable intelligence for someone her age.
bilingual.target: 她这个年纪有着非凡的智力。

bilingual.source: Dwarfism does not affect a person's intelligence.
bilingual.target: 侏儒症并不影响一个人的智力。

bilingual.source: Her intelligence makes her stand out in school.
bilingual.target: 她的智力让她在学校里脱颖而出。

bilingual.source: It's a mistake to equate intelligence with wisdom.
bilingual.target: 把智力等同于智慧是一个错误。

bilingual.source: This test can assess your level of intelligence.
bilingual.target: 这个测试可以评估你的智力水平。

bilingual.source: We need to improve the students' level of intelligence.
bilingual.target: 我们需要提高学生的智力水平。

yingyinNormal.en: But since then, he's been displaying incredible signs of intelligence.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但自那个时候起他就显示出惊人的高智力水平。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Rise of the Planet of the Apes》

yingyinNormal.en: You mean increased intelligence?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你是说智力增长吗？
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Rise of the Planet of the Apes》

yingyinNormal.en: Eight and a half hours of aptitude tests, intelligence tests, personality tests and what do I learn?
yingyinNormal.zh: 8个半小时的天资测验，智力测验，个性测验，我了解了什么？

yingyinNormal.en: Brain's in formation of only a few milligrams, it's not possible to determine any sign of intelligence yet, it acts more as a reflex.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大脑的重量只有几毫克，完全不可能有任何智力的表现，反而比较像是反射作用。

yingyinNormal.en: I wouldn't waste your money on intelligence, attachment or appeal. Unless you'd like to add some pleasure models to your order.
yingyinNormal.zh: 要是我的话我就不会把钱都花在他们智力和颜值上。除非你是想订一批复制人当做性工具。

yingyinNormal.en: I took a tactical risk and I woke that bastard up, believing that his superior intelligence could help us protect ourselves from whatever came at us next.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我冒了一个战略性风险，唤醒了那个混蛋，我以为他超人的智力能保护我们，应对未来任何挑战。

yingyinNormal.en: This is the national intelligence director.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这位是国家情报局主管。

yingyinNormal.en: Where does he come from? He's former British intelligence.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他有什么来头？他是前英国特工。

yingyinNormal.en: Security. We have concerns. Conway has people on House Intelligence.
yingyinNormal.zh: 安全问题，我们有些担忧。康威在众议院情报委员会里有人。

yingyinNormal.en: All of whom can be leveraged. Good old-fashioned human intelligence.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些都可以当筹码，经典的人类智能。

yingyinNormal.en: What's this one? "Bulk apperception"? Basically overall intelligence.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个是什么？"整体统觉"？基本上就是总体智慧。

yingyinNormal.en: Through our intelligence, we, weak humanity, became really very strong.
yingyinNormal.zh: 正因为智慧，弱小的人类变得强大了。

yingyinNormal.en: Attlee said you'd understand. Attlee, your handler in British Intelligence.
yingyinNormal.zh: 艾德礼说你会理解的。艾德礼，你在英国情报机关的上司么。

yingyinNormal.en: And I can't think of a man with greater intelligence than you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不能想象世上有个比你更聪明的人。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, to put some intelligence and culture to our brutal lives.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是啊，想要给我们这种粗人讲点文化知识。

yingyinNormal.en: This is building in all the intelligence that we have to project players.
yingyinNormal.zh: 要建立这些情报，我们必须研究球员。

yingyinNormal.en: Honestly, sir, without proper intelligence, I can't say better than 50/50.
yingyinNormal.zh: 说实话，先生，没有准确情报，我最多只能说一半一半。

yingyinNormal.en: And I imagine this is the very definition of A.I., artificial intelligence?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我猜想这就是所谓人工智能的定义？

yingyinNormal.en: So you're going for artificial intelligence and you don't want to tell the team?
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以你要研究人工智能，还不想告诉团队？

yingyinNormal.en: I am not a loser. Pictionary is not a true test of any real intelligence or skill.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不是失败者，"你画我猜"根本就比不出人的智商和能力。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>

examination_example.sentence: Companies are using artificial <highlight>intelligence</highlight> to remove some of the unconscious bias from hiring decisions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 公司正在利用人工智能来消除招聘决策中的一些无意识偏见。

examination_example.sentence: What is being called artificial general <highlight>intelligence</highlight>, machines that would imitate the way humans think, continues to evade scientists.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 科学家仍然在回避所谓的人工智能，即模仿人类思维方式的机器。

examination_example.sentence: DeepMind is one of the leading artificial <highlight>intelligence</highlight> (AI) companies in the world.
examination_example.sentence_trans: DeepMind是全球领先的人工智能（AI）公司之一。

examination_example.sentence: Furthermore, Scovell's story involved much more than just <highlight>intelligence</highlight> work.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 此外，斯科维尔的故事不仅仅涉及情报工作。

examination_example.sentence: There may have been many spies and <highlight>intelligence</highlight> officers during the Napoleonic Wars.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 拿破仑战争期间可能有许多间谍和情报官员。

examination_example.sentence: In a few decades, artificial <highlight>intelligence</highlight> (AI) will surpass many of the abilities that we believe make us special.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 再过几十年，那些我们自认为与众不同，独一无二的能力都将被人工智能 (AI) 所超越。

examination_example.sentence: New electric engines coupled with artificial <highlight>intelligence</highlight> and autonomous systems will contribute to a more efficient, integrated transport system.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 新的电动发动机加上人工智能和自动系统将有助于建立一个更高效、更一体化的运输系统。

examination_example.sentence: The potential benefits of creating <highlight>intelligence</highlight> are huge. We cannot predict what we might achieve when our own minds are amplified by AI.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 创造智能的潜在好处是巨大的。我们无法预测当人工智能扩大了我们的思维时我们将会实现什么。

examination_example.sentence: A lot of clever people are terrified about artificial <highlight>intelligence</highlight>, fearing that robots will one day become so smart that they'll murder all of us.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 许多聪明人对人工智能感到恐惧，担心有一天机器人会变得非常聪明，以至于他们会杀死我们所有人。

examination_example.sentence: Professor Godel has a much rosier outlook on the future of artificial <highlight>intelligence</highlight> than, say, Elton Musk, Stephen Hawking, Bill Gates or Steve Wozniak.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与埃隆·马斯克(Elon Musk)、斯蒂芬·霍金(Stephen Hawking)、比尔·盖茨(Bill Gates)或史蒂夫·沃兹尼亚克(Steve Wozniak)等人相比，戈德尔教授对人工智能的未来前景要乐观得多。

examination_example.sentence: Professor Shook Godel of Georgia Tech developed an sacrificially intelligent teaching assistant to help handle enormous number of student questions in the online class, Knowledge Based Artificial <highlight>Intelligence</highlight>.

examination_example.sentence: The students, who were studying artificial <highlight>intelligence</highlight>, were interacting with the virtual assistant and couldn't tell it apart om a real human being.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 学习人工智能的学生们与虚拟助手互动，并不知道她不是真人。

examination_example.sentence: Can artificial <highlight>intelligence</highlight> (AI) machines act ethically, meaning can they be honest and fair?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人工智能(AI)机器的行为是否符合道德规范，也就意味着它们能否做到诚实和公平吗？
